A more linear version of the logo also appears as a repeat pattern on silk twill shirts and bags.

Name: dior
Caption: Dior is deeply saddened to learn of the death of Marc Bohan an immense visionary and passionate creator who profoundly marked the history of fashion and of our House where he was Artistic Director for nearly three decades. His extraordinary originality modernity and avant-garde sense of freedom have never ceased to inspire our designers. Our thoughts are with his family and friends.¬†¬†Discussing her admiration MariaGraziaChiuri Creative Director of Dior women?ôs collections comments that ?úMy adolescence and youth were accompanied by the creations of Marc Bohan for Dior. He was a great innovator who succeeded in infusing a charismatic house such as Dior with all the vitality of the sixties fully reflecting the spirit of the times. And by dreaming up with shapes colors and attitude a new way of experiencing fashion and interpreting the body through clothes. When I arrived at Dior I studied his work a lot and he inspired many collections including one with the feminist artist Niki de Saint Phalle who was one of his great friends.?ù¬†¬†For nearly 30 years Marc Bohan guided the House of Dior with creativity and elegance through a constantly evolving world of fashion.¬†His discreet nature directed the spotlight to the women he lovingly and respectfully dressed.¬†His creations reflected not only the era he lived in but over the years they proved also to be timeless .¬†We lost a true master and we?ôre lucky he left us such a rich inheritance. Rest in Peace Mr Bohan said PeterPhilipsMakeup Creative and Image Director of Dior Makeup¬© Association Willy Maywald/ADAGP Paris 2023

Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: Dior is deeply saddened to learn of the death of Marc Bohan an immense visionary and passionate creator who profoundly marked the history of fashion and of our House where he was Artistic Director for nearly three decades. His extraordinary originality modernity and avant-garde sense of freedom have never ceased to inspire our designers. Our thoughts are with his family and friends.¬†¬†For MrKimJones Artistic Director of Dior men?ôs collections ?úMarc Bohan?ôs work is a huge source of surprise and inspiration for what we do. There is always something new to discover whilst researching his work.?ù¬†¬†Meanwhile VictoiredeCastellane Creative Director of Dior Joaillerie remembers how ?úWhen I was 16 I regularly borrowed dresses designed by Marc Bohan for Dior. They were my first ball gowns my first couture memories. His contemporary vision has changed the way we wear clothes the way we look at fashion and style.?ù¬†Francis Kurkdjian Dior Perfume Creation Director evoked his impact saying ?úAfter learning with great sadness of Marc Bohan?ôs passing we must remember how much Dior fragrances owe to his spirit of avant-garde and sophistication of absolute elegance and Parisian chic recognizable at the very first glance. It was during this period that such iconic and daring olfactory signatures as Eau Sauvage and Diorella were launched. His influence is as vivid as ever and his legacy inspiring.?ù¬?Association Willy Maywald/ADAGP Paris 2023¬†¬© Droits re?serve?s

Name: dior

Name: dior

Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: Take your seats as the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2023-2024 show is about to start live on our Instagram account! Name: dior
Caption: Crafted by MariaGraziaChiuri #DiorSS24 melds feminine strength with a nod to history drawing inspiration from Alberto Burris evocative artwork echoed as textured garments featuring elegant distressing frayed finishes and the glow of burnished notes. Designs blur into mystic visions of the Eiffel Tower and the Plan de Paris motif casting a spell of witchy delicacy. Accentuating this narrative the Lady D-Sire and Dior Toujours bags emerge as iconic accessories each enhancing the collections charm with their sophisticated presence.¬© TinaBarney_

Name: dior
Caption: Amidst the bright blue sky photographer RafaelPavarotti_ brings his saturated vision to the new campaign of #DiorSummer23 by MrKimJones. Dreamy pieces feature emblematic House signatures like the Cannage motif seen in its original form and reinvented on the Dior Warp sandal. The collection also introduces new models that celebrate the adventurous spirit of the collection like the Gallagator backpack made in collaboration with MysteryRanch. Visit your nearest Dior boutique or the website via the link in bio for more.

Name: dior
Caption: Against a neutral beige hue the new toile de Jouy Voyage motif from #DiorFall23 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri subtly asserts itself with detailed Indian flora and fauna. Name: dior

Name: dior

With an aesthetic blending new wave beanies with the Phrygian form the traditional cockade is replaced by specially made ronghua velvet flowers a centuries-old savoir-faire originating in Tang dynasty China.

Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: A colorful ode to the founding couturier discover the DiorMaison Cannage Miss Dior collection by CordeliadeCastellane. Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: The ultra-contemporary wardrobe unfurled in the #Dior30Montaigne collection designed by MariaGraziaChiuri adeptly reimagines the visionary aspirations of the Houses founding couturier. Name: dior
Caption: Effortlessly blending elegant and idiosyncratic codes the casual and the classical the youthful treatment of tailoring nods to the style of Black Ivy League students of the 50s and 60s in these looks from the #DiorTears capsule guest designed by DenimTears for the #DiorMenFall 2023 collection by MrKimJones and photographed by DexterNavy for #DiorMagazine 42.

Name: dior

Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: Embodying the contemporary spirit of the #DiorLady9522 by MariaGraziaChiuri Jennifer Lawrence opens up about the satisfaction gained from her work in front of and behind the camera the versatility of her new handbag and how her long-term relationship with the House has been a stimulating source of creative collaboration.¬© Video: TessAyanoPhoto: BrigitteLacombe

Name: dior
Caption: The Houses tailoring #DiorSavoirFaire continues to enjoy the spotlight at the FestivaldeCannes 2023 with a run of #StarsinDior sporting looks by Kim Jones. Name: dior
Caption: Referencing the Houses early years in ready-to-wear with the Miss Dior line the #DiorAW24 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri is redolent with stylistic whispers of the 60s and 70s. Knee-high boots and another hybrid stretch version incorporating a studded Mary Jane element also alluded to the era-appropriate aesthetic.

Name: dior
Caption: Turning heads on the red carpet of LaBiennale #StarsinDior Souheila.Yacoub Jane Campion Alba Rohrwacher Fanny Ardant and AliceIsaaz wore striking Dior looks designed by MariaGraziaChuiri.

Name: dior
Caption: Our coverage surrounding the unveiling of the #DiorCouture Spring-Summer 2024 collection concludes with a focus on one of its more astonishing aspects - an offering of pieces inspired by that most Parisian of icons the trench coat. Utilizing cotton twill MariaGraziaChiuri cut and crafted the classic fabric into outerwear tailoring and a selection of belted dresses and separates including a skirt paired with a top made entirely of hand-crocheted blooms neatly tying together the Houses eternal floral codes with the ever-evolving excellence of #DiorSavoirFaire.¬© LauraSciacovelli

Name: dior
Caption: Indulge in a palette of beauty as you glimpse the latest DiorBeauty design featured in #DiorMagazine 43. Name: dior
Caption: In this new Dior Gardening capsule from #DiorSS23 collection MariaGraziaChiuri revisited the Houses iconic bags like the #LadyDLite and the #DiorBookTote with refreshing botanical embellishments and embroideries that are revealed in cotton or raffia variations. Caption: Architecture and adornment play equally important roles for #DiorCouture Spring-Summer 2024 with MariaGraziaChiuri rethinking the Houses famed tailoring tradition in cotton twill with imposing volumes and simultaneously looking to archival 1950s embroideries with an 18th-century essence for glossy black jet evening embellishments.¬© LauraSciacovelli

Name: dior
Caption: In Mumbai following the unveiling of #DiorFall23 by MariaGraziaChiuri the House has partnered once again with Chanakya.In. Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: Seen here with House friend LaetitiaCasta the new #DiorLady9522 is an irresistible interpretation by MariaGraziaChiuri of the iconic architecture of the #LadyDior. Name: dior
Caption: The #DiorSS24 show by MariaGraziaChiuri explored the theme of deconstructed femininity which was reflected in the makeup look seen on the runway.PeterPhilipsMakeup Creative and Image Director for Dior Makeup created a contrasted look between a translucent complexion and intense lips darkened in the center giving a ?òbitten lip??effect. ¬© OlivierRosePhotography #DiorBeauty #DiorMakeup

Name: dior
Caption: Mark your calendar for the #DiorCruise 2024 show live from Mexico City this Saturday May 20 at 8:30pm CST. Name: dior
Caption: Actress AliWong who scooped the Best Performance by a Female Actor in a Limited Series Anthology Series or TV Movie award for her role in ?úBeef??attended the GoldenGlobes in an elegant draped #DiorCouture creation by MariaGraziaChiuri.¬†#StarsinDior

Name: dior
Caption: Step into a world where fashion and fantasy collide as Dior?ôs Carousel of Dreams at Saks takes you on a mesmerizing journey through time. This exciting collaboration is a tribute to the enduring bonds forged between Dior and New York a legacy spanning over seven decades.Rooted in Christian Dior?ôs profound admiration for the United States the display at Saks weaves a dream of a friendship that encapsulates Dior?ôs essence through all its timeless symbols. Name: dior
Caption: Discover the #DiorAW23 video campaign starring House ambassador JulietteArmanet who performs a special cover of ¬´¬†Non Je ne regrette rien¬†¬ª by Edith Piaf one of the muses behind the collection. Name: dior
Caption: Explore the essence of #DiorCruise 2024 by MariaGraziaChiuri where accessories serve as canvases for artistic reflection. Name: dior
Caption: For #DiorMagazine 42 Irish-born Egyptian artist RafikGreiss takes us on a journey through space and time to the Pyramids of Giza in Egypt to (re)discover the #DiorMenFall 2023 collection by MrKimJones. Inspired by Christian Diors lucky star timeless creations with a futuristic twist are grounded in an exploration of parallels with the ancient world.¬© RafikGreiss

Name: dior
Caption: Trace the enduring bond between Dior and Mexico in A.B.C.Dior?ôs latest feature. From Monsieur Diors original allure with Mexico?ôs lively culture to its splendid evolution nurtured and reimagined under MariaGraziaChiuri culminating in the #DiorCruise 2024 collection this episode references the continuous impact of Mexican traditions and art in shaping Dior?ôs iconic designs. Name: dior
Caption: Take a journey through space and time to the Pyramids of Giza to (re)discover #DiorMenFall by MrKimJones. Inspired by Christian Diors lucky star the collection is grounded in the¬† fascination of parallels with the ancient world. Discover each piece imbued with signature codes of the House now at your nearest boutique or online via the link in bio.¬†¬© Video: FranckLebonPhoto: RafaelPavarotti_

Name: dior
Caption: Paris astronomy and the arcane - all three were the origin of major motifs for #DiorSS24 by MariaGraziaChiuri. Seen in shots taken in the ateliers the French capital is portrayed as a map in the manner of the 18th-century Plan Turgot meticulously placed to retain the uninterrupted street layout across the opening front as well as through a ghostly depiction of the Eiffel Tower from a photograph by BrigitteNiedermairStudio. The night sky meanwhile makes its way into stylized negative prints of suns and moons symbols that also appear as part of the zodiac hand-embroidery of a coat.¬© Sophie Carre

Name: dior
Caption: In a delicate balance between tradition and metamorphosis the #DiorChiffreRouge watch reasserts its singularity through architectural asymmetry with a case that is distinguished by a subtly enlarged and tapered side. Complemented by a red crown and matching hands swirling in a mesmerizing ballet the display embodies the hallmark color of life a deeply intense and characteristic hue as termed by the Houses founding couturier.#DiorHorlogerie ¬© NicholasAlanCope

Name: dior
Caption: Singer-songwriter AliciaKeys was in Mexico City to attend the #DiorCruise 2024 show from MariaGraziaChiuri earlier channeling the powerfully feminine mood wearing a #DiorFall23 look.

Name: dior
Caption: Join House friend KellyWearstler for an exclusive Thanksgiving preparation at her home where she hosts an intimate family gathering amidst the serene backdrop of cypress trees in her garden. Discover her invaluable cooking tips and cherished recipes perfect for the occasion all enhanced by the classic touch of DiorMaison adding a timeless touch to the meals presentation. For a closer look at the thoughtful spread visit Diors YouTube Channel for the full video.¬© Photo: GuelsPhotos

Name: dior
Caption: Discover some of the key accessories of the #DiorSS24 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri from the mysteriously sleek DiorNuit sunglasses to the reimagined Dior Toujours bag presenting a supple crinkled texture. Name: dior
Caption: Zoom in on the new Scarab Bag from the #DiorMenFall 2023 collection by MrKimJones declined in colours inspired by Egypt from a rocky grey to a sandy shade inspired by the Great Pyramids of Giza which served as the backdrop for the show. Inspired by the big outdoors the hi-tech creation which features a Christian Dior strap on which to fasten accessories is now available to discover online or in your nearest Dior boutique.¬© AndreaCenetiempo

Name: dior
Caption: The #DiorWinter23 campaign masterfully interprets one of the collection?ôs main storylines where an old world meets a new one in change and in flux. Blending poetic simplicity and extreme precision a quest for elegance comfort and functionality pervades the collection. Declined in a sea of grays silhouettes are softened curved and malleable while clothes are hybridized and metamorphosed from the Passe Partout coat in Donegal tweed with zipped open sleeves to nods to British tailoring traditions and materials that evoke a haute couture tailleur.¬© RafaelPavarotti_

Name: dior
Caption: Delve into the imaginative world of ZadieXa with her contribution to the 8th edition of the #DiorLadyArt project. Reimagining the #LadyDior the artist infuses traditional Korean handicraft techniques into her signature collage style presented through a lively contemporary prism. The bags boast intricate details including mother-of-pearl applications that offer a glimpse into the artist?ôs fantastical universe complete with sculpted tiger heads and ethereal landscapes filled with 3D silk flowers.¬© Photo: MarionBerrin

Name: dior
Caption: Bold black styles a hue beloved by the founding couturier daringly contrast with the vibrant looks of #DiorFall23 by MariaGraziaChiuri for a collection that boasts a Parisian wardrobe with Indian influences. The iconic toile de Jouy and #DiorBarJacket are revisited along with new creations like the CD Oval bag available at your nearest Dior boutique or online via the link in bio.¬© VivianeSassenStudio

Name: dior
Caption: The #LadyDior Celebration exhibition plays host to a retrospective featuring forty-two reinterpretations by twenty-four renowned Korean artists among these talents hear from artists LeeKunYong79 LeeHunChung_Studio YesumYesum and ZadieXa. Within the #LadyDiorAsSeenBy and #DiorLadyArt projects their collective efforts shine a spotlight on the intricate savoir-faire encapsulated within the House exemplifying the epitome of this iconic accessory.¬© Video : Albert.Film Photo: Kyungsub Shin

Name: dior
Caption: Frolic in the universe of the new Dior Gardening capsule from the #DiorSS23 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri. Festive motifs flourish across ready-to-wear items and accessories like the Dior Petites Fleurs and Dior Birds prints or the L?ôunion fait la force crest of the Dior Union theme.¬© EllenVonUnwerth

Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: Embark on a magical adventure with the bucolic BabyDior Autumn-Winter 2023-2024 collection by CordeliadeCastellane. Name: dior
Caption: Discover a treasury of delights in the latest #DiorCruise 2024 designed by MariaGraziaChiuri where accessories now hold an animated spirit displaying the reimagined toile de Jouy by PietroRuffoArtist enhanced by colorful prints populated by the lush Mexican flora and fauna. Name: dior
Caption: See the making of Avani.Rai?ôs shoot for #DiorMagazine 42. Patterned with the Jardin Indien and Toile de Jouy Voyage motifs dreamy silk essentials from the #DiorFall23 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri are captured in an enchanting Indian setting.¬© Video: FLPDiary

Name: dior
Caption: Dior is delighted to announce an unprecedented long-term collaboration with Anne-Sophie Pic the most Michelin-starred female chef in the world. Name: dior
Caption: Depicting the contours of a clean-cut diamond the CD initials are transformed into a mesmerizing motif emblematic of the Dior legacy. Name: dior
Caption: Within the pages of #DiorMagazine 43 the #DiorAW23 collection dreamed up by MariaGraziaChiuri shines through with a curated selection of iconic pieces. Caption: Delve into the A.B.C.Dior series where ?òC??for Cuisine highlights the unique interplay between the House and the culinary arts. Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: The #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2023-2024 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri was unveiled on Monday afternoon in Paris. Name: dior
Caption: Dreamed up by VictoiredeCastellane the La D My Dior reflects the multiple facets of femininity in its daring dimensions and the finest materials. Name: dior

Name: dior
Caption: For #DiorSummer24 MrKimJones opted for opposing kinds of decoration. On the one hand little metal rings studded pieces in an all-over abundance with tonally minimalistic impact. Name: dior
Caption: Welcome to an imaginative playground where contemporary art fuses with fashion in the charming limited-edition capsule by MrKimJones crafted in collaboration with Japanese artist Ota539. Caption: May 1st is one of the House?ôs favorite traditions honoring Monsieur Dior?ôs lucky charm - the lily of the valley flower - and the emblem of fine weather. Name: dior

Name: dior

Caption: Join Ana√Øs Demoustier President of the Cam√©ra d?ôOr Jury at the FestivaldeCannes in a delightful ice cream challenge with Dior as she shares her serendipitous acting journey Cannes red carpet debut and the deep emotions and lasting memories associated with a stunning Dior dress on the grand stage! Name: dior
Caption: Re-experience the #DiorCouture Autumn-Winter 2023-2024 show unveiling the new collection by MariaGraziaChiuri which looks afresh at the apparent familiarity of Greco-Roman mythology and costume to reimagine the characteristic forms and colors through a truly contemporary prism and the excellence of #DiorSavoirFaire. ¬© Scenographic artworks by Marti.Nin embroideries by Chanakya.In and Chanakya.School.Music: ¬´¬†To Be Honest¬†¬ª by ChristineandtheQueens

Name: dior
Caption: The essence of ballet legend Rudolf Nureyev emanates from a video distilling some of the masterful details that define #DiorWinter24 by MrKimJones. Emerging alongside pieces that trace a more direct link to the world of dance standout couture creations showcase faint-making examples of #DiorSavoirFaire from the silver uchikake kimono handmade in Japan to the cascade of crystal fringe on a top and the perfectly judged proportions of artfully wrapped trousers. ¬© Jackie_Nickerson

Name: dior
Caption: The figure of Italian artist-designer Gabriella Crespi encapsulates the essence of #DiorAW24. Ceaselessly creative as her daughter Elisabetta explains her work caught the attention of Marc Bohan around the time he launched the House?ôs ready-to-wear line and accompanying eponymous boutique Miss Dior. Looking back at that era as inspiration for this new collection MariaGraziaChiuri picks up the thread detailing how Crespi epitomized the Miss Dior woman with her independence energy and instinctive sense of style. ¬© Video: MelindaTrianaAll rights reserved by Archivio Gabriella Crespi¬© BBC Motion Gallery/Getty Images

Name: dior
Caption: Three looks from Tuesdays #DiorSS24 show place Paris as an anchor for the new collection¬† by MariaGraziaChiuri. Around a coat hazily printed with a map of the French capital two shoulder-baring outfits reprise the distinctive style of the archival 1948 dress Abandon testifying to a continuity and evolution in how the House powerfully frames femininity.¬© Photo: LauraSciacovelliElena Bellantoni NOT HER digital installation 2023

Name: dior
Caption: In its 8th iteration a new year unveils fresh creative horizons in the #DiorLadyArt project where artists from around the world unite to reinterpret the iconic #LadyDior including ZadieXa LeeKunYong79 LNkoth and MickaleneThomas. Witness as these celebrated artists reinterpret this iconic fashion accessory blending heritage with their unique creative visions transforming the #LadyDior into an extraordinary work of art. Stay tuned for an in-depth exploration of each artist?ôs journey and the remarkable metamorphosis of this enduring symbol of style.

Name: dior
Caption: Take your seats for the #DiorWinter24 show from MrKimJones live on our Instagram account! In the final moments before the collection is revealed go behind the scenes to discover the balletic score specially arranged by MaxRichterMusic.¬© Video: MelindaTrianaMusic: MaxRichterMusic StudioRichterMahr

Name: dior
Caption: The #DiorSS24 collection by MariaGraziaChiuri channels the rebellious and unconventional women in history its dark undercurrent expressed primarily in black brightened with lighter hues. Innovatively textured materials reference passing time incorporating iconography of the French capital mixing nature with esoterica. Providing the show backdrop ?òNOT HER??a monumental digital artwork by Ele.Bellantoni_Studio takes on misogynistic advertising.

Name: dior
Caption: Express yourself with the myriad colors and materials of the ?òTribales Rose des Vents??earrings. Two iconic #DiorJoaillerie collections by VictoiredeCastellane come together in a creative fusion showcased here by actress Julia_deNunez. The characteristic double earrings combine the talismanic wind rose motif in gold with twinkling white diamonds and ornamental stones including onyx malachite and mother-of-pearl. Tap the link in bio to uncover the extensive offering.¬© TylersPhotos

Name: dior
Caption: Discover the 8th edition of the #DiorLadyArt project an enthralling narrative woven around the House?ôs iconic bag. A symbol of timeless allure and a storied legacy the #LadyDior continually redefines itself now in the artistic hands of ArtistandGal XuZhen8848 Hilary_Pecis_Art and GilbertandGeorgeCentre. This collaboration seamlessly embodies the very spirit of Diors ethos a tribute to the fervor of creativity and the depth of emotions.

Name: dior
Caption: We wrap up our coverage of the #DiorWinter24 by MrKimJones show with a final trio of looks that convey the modernity of the collection?ôs ability to tap into the House?ôs heritage in a totally contemporary way. A jacket wide across the torso and the sleeve-like wrap nonchalantly worn around a double-face coat are wholly new rewritings of decades-old designs contained in the archives while the sporty ingenuity of a double-layered blouson with integrated gilet is purely and resolutely of now. ¬© Brett_Lloyd

Name: dior
Caption: Deeply rooted in its historic design the #DiorChiffreRouge goes beyond mere timekeeping. Glimpse the mechanical heart through transparent casings showcasing the technical dimensions of its inner workings. Enhanced with the iconic lines of cannage these micro-textured graphics adorn both the dial and oscillating weight. Meanwhile the presence of intricate gears and balance springs serves as a testament to the diverse range of calibers magnifying a steadfast commitment to horological excellence.¬© Piotr_Stoklosa

Name: dior
Caption: Check out the #DiorSki capsule from #DiorSpring24 by MrKimJones pushing the limits of performance in a range of state-of-the-art ski gear designed in collaboration with the Japanese brand Descente_International including a short ski parka and a sky-blue down ski jacket and matching ski pants. Our Artistic Director this season also reconnects with the Swedish snow sports and protection specialist POCSports on two helmet designs and a pair of goggles inspired by the world of racing as well as AK.SKI which produced an exclusive snowboard featuring a reproduction of a bewitching artwork by PeterDoig exalting the beauty of winter landscapes. ¬© Jackie_Nickerson

Name: dior
Caption: We wrap up our week of #DiorSS24 show coverage with three two-tone looks by MariaGraziaChiuri distilling the duality of a collection offering a contemporary wardrobe for women that draws its essence from historical predecessors who rewrote the rules. With an eased up revisiting of the #DiorBarJacket and tailoring in general an archive-referencing shirt and a digital print of the Eiffel Tower from a BrigitteNiedermairStudio photo the enduring image is of a Parisienne who is as modern as she is international.¬© LauraSciacovelliElena Bellantoni NOT HER digital installation 2023

Name: dior
Caption: Relive the finale of the #DiorSS24 show presenting the new collection by MariaGraziaChiuri a darkly exhilarating ode to trailblazing and unconventional women held amid an extraordinary scenographic installation titled NOT HER by Ele.Bellantoni_Studio. As the last look out a body-skimming lace dress appropriately in black makes a proud declaration of unapologetic femininity incorporating floral elements that trace a direct line between the inspiration and the House?ôs fundamental codes. Stay tuned as our coverage continues with a close-up shift in focus to the essential design details that make this lineup a standout of the season.¬© Elena Bellantoni NOT HER digital installation 2023

Name: dior
Caption: Ever wondered what Jessie Buckleys favorite movie quote is? Name: dior
Caption: Take to the slopes this winter with the #DiorSki capsule from #DiorSpring24 by MrKimJones featuring artworks by PeterDoig. Discover the full range from a short ski parka to ski goggles and a snowboard available in stores and on Dior.com. ¬© Photo: Jackie_NickersonMusic : Clark ??Lambent Rag

Name: dior
Caption: Explore the parley.tv movement up close in our global documentary series The Air We Breathe and meet the inspiring people on the ground who are working tirelessly to protect our oceans. So far the series has traveled to Australia South Africa Hawaii and Chile to tell our story through the eyes of the activists scientists Indigenous leaders surfers volunteers and marine biologists who are all crucial to our mission.Each episode explores our work intercepting marine plastic pollution but also the deeper connections we have formed with local and Indigenous communities ??people who have stewarded the land and seas for millenia and ultimately hold the key to their survival.Welcome into our world wed love you to be part of this story too. Jump in and join the movement at parley.tv and then head to youtube.com/parleychannel to see the full films.

Name: dior
Caption: The artist Ele.Bellantoni_Studio talks about ?òNOT HER??the monumental digital installation she created especially for the #DiorSS24 show by MariaGraziaChiuri in Paris. Caption: Make Primark sugar cookies with jemmaloi ?íô?ÑÔ∏è #Primark‚¨áÔ∏èWhat you?ôll need ?ç™:350g plain flour100g self-raising flour130g softened cubed butter130g golden syrup130g granulated sugar1 tsp vanilla extract1 egg beaten450g Royal Icing Sugar75ml waterFood colouringHow to ?ßë?çüç?Cookies??Combine both flours and sugar in a large mixing bowl then add the cubed butter. Rub together between your fingers until it resembles a sand like consistency. ??Make a well in the centre and add the egg golden syrup and vanilla extract. Mix to combine and then bring together into two small dough balls. Lay each ball of dough between two sheets of greaseproof paper and roll to about 0.5mm thick. Chill in the fridge for 30-60 minutes. ??Pre heat your oven to 170¬∞c and line two trays with greaseproof paper. Remove the dough from the fridge and cut out your cookie shapes laying them on the trays. Bake for 8-10 minutes and allow to cool completely before decorating. Icing: ??Combine both ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat at a medium-high speed until the consistency resembles toothpaste. Use as many small bowls as you need colours and add food colouring to each one until you have your desired shade. Add half of each colour to piping bags and put to one side. These are for the outlines. With the remaining icing colours add little amounts of water until you have a thinner consistency to ?òflood??in between your outlines. Put these in piping bags too.  ??To ice your biscuits snip a tiny hole at the end of your piping bags and begin by creating an outline with your thicker icing you will then use the flood icing to colour in your outlines. ??Leave to dry overnight or in a low oven for 30 minutes.

Caption: Home-made roasted nuts ?•ú #Primark #DIY?®¬†‚¨áÔ∏è‚Ä®¬†What you need for Roasted Nuts?å∞:?®¬?00g grams of plain mixed nuts.1 tbsp of butter40ml water75g caster sugar1 tsp sweet paprika¬Ω tsp ground black pepper1 tsp fine salt¬†How to ?ßë?çüç??®¬†‚Ä¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉPre heat the oven to 180c and line a large tray with greaseproof paper.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉAdd the nuts to medium sized bowl and add the black pepper sweet paprika salt and stir to combine.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉHeat the butter sugar and water in a small pan until the sugar has just dissolved (1-2 minutes on a medium heat)?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉPour over your nuts and stir well ensuring they are evenly coated.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉSpread out on the baking tray and roast in the oven for 15 minutes stirring halfway through.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉAllow to cool slightly before handling.?®¬†What you need for Cheesy Puff Stars ??:?®¬†‚Ä¢‚ÄÉ‚Ä? roll of ready-made puff pastry.?¢‚ÄÉ‚Ä?0g grated cheddar cheese mixed with 15g parmesan.?¢‚ÄÉ‚Ä?-3 tbsp milk?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉSeasoning of your choice?®¬†How to ?ßë?çüç?¬†?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉPre heat the oven to 180c and line two baking trays with greaseproof paper.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉRemove the puff pastry from the pack and unroll. Sprinkle evenly with the grated cheese reserving about a quarter of it.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉFold the puff pastry in half and roll back to original size on a floured worktop.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉUsing a star pastry cutter cut out as many shapes as you can.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉTransfer your star shapes to a baking tray and brush the tops with milk.?¢‚ÄÉ‚ÄÉSprinkle a little of the remaining cheese on top followed by seasoning of your choice and bake for 10-12 minutes.

Caption: Breakfast Tray Bake ??#Primark #DIYWhat you need ?•ò:??500g small baby potatoes cubed??1 x 400g can of baked beans??100g mushrooms sliced??A handful of fresh sage leaves (or 1 tsp dried sage)??8-10 vine tomatoes or 4 large tomatoes halved??4 eggs??8 pigs in blankets??2 tbsp olive oil??Salt and pepper How to ?ßë?çüç???Pre heat oven to 200c and prepare a large oven proof tray??In a small bowl toss the potatoes in 1 tablespoon of oil and season with salt and pepper spreading out evenly on the tray. ??Transfer to the oven for 20 minutes.??In the same bowl add the mushrooms second tablespoon of olive oil mushrooms and sage. ??Season stir and add to the tray with the potatoes. ??Add the pigs in blankets and return to the oven for a further 20 minutes.??Split the can of beans between two oven safe pots then nestle between the other ingredients on the tray. ??Make small wells amongst the ingredients for the eggs and carefully crack them into the wells.??Return the tray to the oven for a final 10 minutes and prepare your Festive breakfast table!

Caption: Come with jo_the_futurist to our #PrimarkCares event ?íô .Primark Cares has nine commitments across three key areas ??product planet and people. These commitments range from making all our clothes from recycled or more sustainably sourced materials by 2030 halving carbon emissions across our supply chain over the next seven years and pursuing a living wage for workers in our supply chain. All of the decor for the event was repurposed from other events and included QR codes and information about the programme. The food was sourced locally to minimise the event?ôs impact and everyone was invited to take home leftovers to minimise food waste. We welcomed influencers and the press to talk about the programme and open up an important conversation about the impact of fashion.
